Section Header: Gently loosen the neoGuardTM device every 4 to 6 hours and examine the newborn's forehead for any signs of skin irritation. If you observe any signs of an adverse event such as a rash or potential burn, please remove the device completely and inform the pediatrician/neonatologist or medical officer. Please record your observations for every safety check performed by indicating the time and filling in the corresponding number code: 1 = No remarkable findings, 2 = Rash, 3 = Infection, 4 = Burn, 5 = Other skin irritation (please specify)
